
Overview of verb allot

The verb allot has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (6) assign, allot, portion -- (give out; "We were assigned new uniforms")
2. (4) accord, allot, grant -- (allow to have; "grant a privilege")
3. (2) distribute, administer, mete out, deal, parcel out, lot, dispense, shell out, deal out, dish out, allot, dole out -- (administer or bestow, as in small portions; "administer critical remarks to everyone present"; "dole out some money"; "shell out pocket money for the children"; "deal a blow to someone"; "the machine dispenses soft drinks")
